<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/481.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to the
                                    Dominican Republic</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs requests me to inform you that
                                Peynado<note n="5" xml:id="d549fn5">Dominican Minister to the United
                                States.</note> will leave for Washington in a few days with full
                            general powers to sign a boundary protocol that will be submitted to
                            plebiscite.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>